com.tomtom.speedtools.akka

Class TypedActorFactory<T,Impl extends T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tomtom.speedtools.akka.TypedActorFactory<T,Impl>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    akka.japi.Creator<Impl>, Serializable

    public class TypedActorFactory<T,Impl extends T>
extends Object
implements akka.japi.Creator<Impl>
    Since the class implements Creator, instances can be used to construct TypedProps objects. As a convenience, the static actorOf methods can be used to create an actor from this factory directly. These convenience methods can be used when no TypedProps.withDispatcher(String) or other Props specifics are necessary.
    See Also:
